---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import LabSignup from '../../components/LabSignup.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AI Visibility Audit | Editorial Intelligence"
  description="Understand how AI systems describe your organisation, why competitors appear ahead of you and what needs to change for your expertise to become easier to find, verify and recommend."
  ogDescription="Understand how AI systems describe your organisation, why competitors appear ahead of you and what needs to change for your expertise to become easier to find, verify and recommend."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="ava-inner">

      <!-- Hero -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">AI Visibility Audit</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">Become a source AI systems can understand, trust and recommend.</h1>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Understand how AI systems describe your organisation, why competitors appear ahead of you and what needs to change for your expertise to become easier to find, verify and recommend.</p>
          <p>The AI Visibility Audit examines the evidence, expertise, narratives and content structures behind your visibility in AI-generated answers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-ctas">
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=AI%20Visibility%20Audit%20enquiry" class="ava-btn">Discuss an AI Visibility Audit</a>
          <a href="/frameworks/ai-search-visibility" class="ava-link">Read the AI search framework →</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Problem section -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-6">AI visibility is not only a search problem</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Organisations are beginning to ask why competitors appear in ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews and other AI-generated answers while they do not.</p>
          <p>The temptation is to treat this as an optimisation problem: publish more pages, add FAQs, adjust metadata. Those actions may help at the margins. They cannot compensate for an organisation whose knowledge is fragmented, generic or difficult to verify.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ava-list mb-8">
          <li>Valuable research is published once and then disappears.</li>
          <li>Customer evidence is scattered across unrelated pages.</li>
          <li>Subject-matter expertise is not clearly visible.</li>
          <li>The organisation has content but no recognisable position.</li>
          <li>Individual pages exist, but they do not form a connected body of knowledge.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prose-note">The audit identifies the editorial and knowledge-system problems beneath the visibility problem.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- What you leave with -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-4">What you leave with</h2>
        <p class="prose-intro mb-8">Six concrete deliverables, shaped around your market, priority topics and available evidence.</p>

        <div class="deliverables-list mb-6">

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">01</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">AI visibility baseline</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">A documented view of how selected AI systems currently represent the organisation across agreed priority questions.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">02</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">Competitor comparison</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">A focused comparison showing where competitors are more visible, more clearly positioned or better supported by evidence.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">03</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">Evidence and authority map</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">A map of the research, expertise, customer proof, frameworks and external signals currently supporting the organisation's authority.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">04</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">Narrative gap analysis</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">An assessment of the arguments the organisation wants to own, the claims it can currently support and the gaps preventing a coherent position.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">05</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">Knowledge-system assessment</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">A review of whether relevant content works as a connected body of knowledge or as a collection of isolated assets.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">06</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">Prioritised 90-day roadmap</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">A practical sequence of quick wins, foundational changes and longer-term opportunities.</p>
          </div>

        </div>

        <p class="scope-note">The exact scope is agreed before the audit and shaped around your market, priority topics and available evidence.</p>

        <!--
          SAMPLE OUTPUT PLACEHOLDER
          A sample AI visibility baseline and evidence map will be added here
          once a founding engagement is complete and the client has given permission
          to share an anonymised extract. Replace this comment with the asset when ready.
        -->
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- What the audit assesses -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-4">What the audit assesses</h2>
        <p class="prose-intro mb-8">Six connected areas that together reveal how visible, credible and recommendable the organisation currently is.</p>

        <div class="assess-grid">

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">AI answer visibility</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Presence in relevant AI-generated answers</li>
              <li>Accuracy of company descriptions</li>
              <li>Topic and category association</li>
              <li>Citations and source patterns</li>
              <li>Competitor visibility</li>
              <li>Brand and product confusion</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">Evidence strength</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Original research</li>
              <li>Customer evidence and case studies</li>
              <li>Data and proprietary insight</li>
              <li>Named experts</li>
              <li>External corroboration</li>
              <li>Clear sourcing</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">Narrative distinctiveness</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Recognisable strategic positions</li>
              <li>Named concepts and frameworks</li>
              <li>Consistency of language</li>
              <li>Defensible claims</li>
              <li>Clear market point of view</li>
              <li>Evidence supporting each argument</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">Knowledge architecture</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Connections between related content</li>
              <li>Topic clusters and pathways</li>
              <li>Internal linking</li>
              <li>Content discoverability</li>
              <li>Duplication and fragmentation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">Expertise signals</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Visible authorship</li>
              <li>Subject-matter expert participation</li>
              <li>Leadership perspectives</li>
              <li>Author and organisation credibility</li>
              <li>Consistent expertise across channels</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">Buyability</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Whether AI can explain what the organisation does</li>
              <li>Whether differentiation is clear</li>
              <li>Whether proof supports commercial claims</li>
              <li>Whether use cases and audiences are explicit</li>
              <li>Whether visibility connects to a plausible buying decision</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>

        <p class="assess-note">Buyability assessment draws on the <a href="/frameworks/ai-visibility-buyability" class="ava-inline-link">AI Visibility and Buyability framework</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Typical engagement -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-6">Typical engagement</h2>
        <div class="engagement-panel">
          <div class="prose-section">
            <p>A focused audit covering an agreed set of commercial topics, priority questions and competitors.</p>
            <p>Typically delivered over two to three weeks, with a written report, evidence map and findings session.</p>
            <p>The scope and fixed fee are agreed in advance. The final report brings together the visibility baseline, competitor findings, evidence map, narrative gaps, knowledge-system findings and 90-day roadmap.</p>
          </div>
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=AI%20Visibility%20Audit%20enquiry" class="ava-btn mt-6 inline-flex">Discuss an AI Visibility Audit</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- How the audit works -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-8">How the audit works</h2>
        <div class="process-steps">

          <div class="process-step">
            <span class="process-num">1</span>
            <div class="process-content">
              <h3 class="process-heading">Define the territory</h3>
              <p class="process-body">Agree the priority audiences, commercial topics, competitors and questions the organisation wants to be associated with.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="process-step">
            <span class="process-num">2</span>
            <div class="process-content">
              <h3 class="process-heading">Test current visibility</h3>
              <p class="process-body">Review how selected AI systems answer those questions and which organisations, sources and evidence appear.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="process-step">
            <span class="process-num">3</span>
            <div class="process-content">
              <h3 class="process-heading">Audit the knowledge system</h3>
              <p class="process-body">Assess the organisation's evidence, narratives, expertise, content relationships and commercial clarity.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="process-step">
            <span class="process-num">4</span>
            <div class="process-content">
              <h3 class="process-heading">Set the roadmap</h3>
              <p class="process-body">Present the findings, prioritise the changes and identify what should be improved over the following 90 days.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Who it is for -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-4">Who this is for</h2>
        <p class="prose-intro mb-6">B2B organisations whose credibility depends on being understood in complex or competitive markets.</p>
        <ul class="ava-list mb-6">
          <li>SaaS and enterprise technology companies</li>
          <li>Fintech and financial services organisations</li>
          <li>Professional services firms</li>
          <li>Research-led organisations</li>
          <li>Companies investing in thought leadership</li>
          <li>Startups and scaleups entering established categories</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prose-note mb-4">It is particularly useful when you already have substantial content or evidence but cannot see it translating into authority, visibility or differentiation.</p>
        <p class="prose-note">The work is typically commissioned by marketing, content, communications, research, product marketing or founder-led teams.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- What this is not -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-6">What this audit is not</h2>
        <ul class="not-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Not a guarantee of rankings, citations or AI inclusion.</strong>
            AI-generated answers vary by system, prompt, geography and time. The audit improves the underlying signals — it cannot guarantee a fixed position.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Not only a technical SEO audit.</strong>
            Technical accessibility matters, but this service focuses on knowledge quality, evidence, expertise and narrative. Those are editorial problems, not primarily technical ones.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Not automatically a recommendation to publish more.</strong>
            The answer may be to connect, strengthen or better evidence what already exists.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Not based on prompt manipulation.</strong>
            The goal is lasting authority, not temporary tricks that influence individual AI outputs.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Why Editorial Intelligence -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-6">Why Editorial Intelligence</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-6">
          <p>AI systems are better able to understand organisations whose knowledge is connected, evidenced and distinctively their own.</p>
          <p>Editorial Intelligence provides the underlying method: identifying useful signals, interpreting what they mean, developing defensible narratives and connecting evidence into a body of knowledge that compounds over time.</p>
          <p>The AI Visibility Audit applies that method to a specific commercial question: can AI systems confidently understand what your organisation knows, why it is credible and when it should be recommended?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ei-links">
          <a href="/intelligence" class="ei-link">What is Editorial Intelligence →</a>
          <a href="/editorial-intelligence-os" class="ei-link">Editorial Intelligence OS →</a>
          <a href="/frameworks/ai-search-visibility" class="ei-link">AI search framework →</a>
          <a href="/frameworks/ai-visibility-buyability" class="ei-link">AI Visibility and Buyability →</a>
          <a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="ei-link">Hidden Hours — in practice →</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Lab signup -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <LabSignup headline="Follow the AI visibility work" />
      </div>

      <!-- Founding engagements -->
      <section class="founding-section mb-16">
        <h2 class="founding-heading mb-4">Founding audit engagements</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-6">
          <p>I am opening a small number of founding engagements to apply and refine the audit with B2B organisations facing real AI visibility questions.</p>
          <p>Founding clients receive the complete audit, findings session and prioritised roadmap. I will also ask for candid feedback and, where appropriate, permission to document the engagement as an anonymised or attributed case study.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=AI%20Visibility%20Audit%20enquiry" class="ava-btn">Discuss a founding audit</a>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-8">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Which AI systems do you assess?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>The exact mix is agreed according to the organisation's market and priority audiences. It may include ChatGPT, Google's AI experiences and Perplexity, depending on where buyers are most likely to encounter AI-generated answers. The audit does not rely on access to private model data.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Can you guarantee that we will appear in AI answers?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>No. AI outputs vary by system, prompt, geography and time. The audit improves the underlying signals that make an organisation easier to understand, verify and recommend — which is the condition for sustained visibility, not a shortcut to it.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Is this the same as SEO?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>It overlaps with search in some areas — content architecture, technical accessibility and topical coverage all matter. But this service focuses on evidence quality, expertise signals, narrative consistency and how well the organisation's knowledge holds together. Those are editorial questions, not primarily technical ones.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Do we need a large content library?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>No. A smaller body of original, well-connected and credible material can be more useful than a large volume of generic content. The audit assesses what you have, not how much of it there is.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Will you implement the recommendations?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Implementation support can be scoped separately — narrative development, evidence mapping, content architecture or editorial-system work. The audit is a complete engagement in itself; further work is available but not required.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Is this suitable for startups?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes, particularly where a startup needs to establish category association, clarify differentiation or turn founder and customer insight into visible authority. Clarity about what the organisation does needs to come before visibility — the audit is not a substitute for product-market fit.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Final CTA -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-4">Find out what AI can — and cannot — confidently say about your organisation.</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Establish your current visibility, identify the authority gaps beneath it and create a practical plan for becoming a more credible and recommendable source.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="final-ctas">
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=AI%20Visibility%20Audit%20enquiry" class="ava-btn">Discuss an AI Visibility Audit</a>
          <a href="/frameworks/ai-search-visibility" class="ava-link">Explore the AI search framework →</a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ava-inner {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  /* ── Prose ── */
  .prose-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .prose-intro {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .prose-note {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .mb-4 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  /* ── Headings ── */
  .ava-h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.5vw, 1.4rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  /* ── CTAs ── */
  .hero-ctas,
  .final-ctas {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .ava-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-surface);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .ava-btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; }

  .mt-6 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }

  .ava-link {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }

  .ava-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .ava-inline-link {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 35%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .ava-inline-link:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

  /* ── Lists ── */
  .ava-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ava-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .ava-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .ava-list-sm {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .ava-list-sm li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .ava-list-sm li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* ── Deliverables ── */
  .deliverables-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .deliverable-item {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
  }

  .deliverable-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .deliverable-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .deliverable-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.7;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .deliverable-heading {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .deliverable-body {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: calc(0.5625rem * 2 + 0.75rem);
  }

  .scope-note {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── Assessment grid ── */
  .assess-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--color-rule);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 540px) {
    .assess-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }

  @media (min-width: 800px) {
    .assess-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; }
  }

  .assess-category {
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .assess-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .assess-note {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── Typical engagement ── */
  .engagement-panel {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
  }

  .engagement-panel .prose-section p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  /* ── Process ── */
  .process-steps {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .process-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
  }

  .process-step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .process-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.7;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
    min-width: 1rem;
  }

  .process-heading {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .process-body {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── What this is not ── */
  .not-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
